<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span id="coordinates"><a href="/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_system" title="Geographic coordinate system">Coordinates</a>: <span class="plainlinks nourlexpansion"><a class="external text" href="//tools.wmflabs.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Chalford&amp;params=51.72383_N_-2.14907_E_region:GB_type:city(6215)"><span class="geo-nondefault"><span class="geo-dms" title="Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location"><span class="latitude">51°43′26″N</span> <span class="longitude">2°08′57″W</span></span></span><span class="geo-multi-punct">﻿ / ﻿</span><span class="geo-default"><span class="geo-dec" title="Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location">51.72383°N 2.14907°W</span><span style="display:none">﻿ / <span class="geo">51.72383; -2.14907</span></span></span></a></span></span></span></p>
<p><b>Chalford</b> is a village in the <a href="/wiki/River_Frome,_Stroud" title="River Frome, Stroud">Frome Valley</a> of the <a href="/wiki/Cotswolds" title="Cotswolds">Cotswolds</a> in <a href="/wiki/Gloucestershire" title="Gloucestershire">Gloucestershire</a>, <a href="/wiki/England" title="England">England</a>. It is about 8&#160;km upstream (4 miles east) of <a href="/wiki/Stroud,_Gloucestershire" title="Stroud, Gloucestershire" class="mw-redirect">Stroud</a>. It gives its name to Chalford <a href="/wiki/Parish_(country_subdivision)" title="Parish (country subdivision)" class="mw-redirect">parish</a>, which covers the villages of Chalford, Chalford Hill, France Lynch, Bussage and Brownshill, spread over 2&#160;mi² (5&#160;km²) of the Cotswold countryside. At this point the valley is also called the <a href="/wiki/Five_Valleys" title="Five Valleys">Golden Valley</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p></p>
<div id="toc" class="toc">
